Output is `{"name":"Jane","age":30}` ✅

Here's the complete `Program.cs`:

```csharp
using System.Text.Json;

var person = new Person("Jane", 30);

var options = new JsonSerializerOptions
{
    PropertyNamingPolicy = JsonNamingPolicy.CamelCase
};

Console.WriteLine(JsonSerializer.Serialize(person, options));

public record Person(string Name, int Age);
```

The key is `JsonNamingPolicy.CamelCase` — it converts PascalCase property names (`Name`, `Age`) to camelCase (`name`, `age`) during serialization.
